<br>
Earrings: Your HP seem rather low. You'll need to keep these for now.<br>
<br>
Neck: You don't need AGI (you'll have some on your equipment so trust me on this...) or DEX (DEX isn't as important as AC/HP). Get either: Rygorr (has STA for extra HP, has svmagic and 9 AC) or Spider Fur (10 AC and some STR with saves) Rygorr will cost you 100ppish, Spider Fur 500<br>
<br>
Face: Get better... either fine plate mask (70pp or less) or cystal spider eyes (1kpp)<br>
<br>
Rings: Get 1 shadel bandit ring (1.5k, maybe 1k) and 1 6AC 65HP ring (450-500pp)<br>
<br>
Bracers: Deepwater. (1k each)<br>
<br>
Arms: Deepwater. (1k)<br>
<br>
Gaunts: Thunder Etched (2k)<br>
<br>
Shoulder: Tattered (250pp) or Crested (250-400pp). Tattered will give 1 more AC, Crested will give ~15 more HP (go with the HP for now, your HP are a little low. Once you get more HP stuff, consider going for tattered)<br>
<br>
Cloak: Oh dear, hehe. I had your cloak for the longest time. Get Spider Fur (500pp) or white bear pelt cloak (still goes for as much as 8kpp)<br>
<br>
Belt: You got FBSS, good enough for now. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Legs: These are a pain to upgrade. <br>
Option 1: Buy sebscale (3k) or kylong (1k).<br>
Option 2: Hunt in KC, and loot Jarsath leggings (free)<br>
<br>
Boots: Deepwater (1k)<br>
<br>
Weapon: For pete's sake, get at least an Axe of Frost.... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
OK Seriously now. Get an ACG for 2hs (1-2kpp), a Centi warspear for piercing (300pp), a shaded blade for 1hs (2kpp), a goranga club for 1hb (drops in Maiden's, nodrop), some kind of 2hb (varying prices <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) for 2hb. Get a crusty shield to go with your 1hers (150pp) or a Clay Guardian Shield (300-500pp)<br>
<br>
Range slot: Lookin' good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Get a Bow of the Forlorn for long-range low-aggro pulling (free from the Huntmaster in the Warrens, or buy very cheap) and some 1 dmg 150 range arrows (make them yourself with a fletching kit, not expensive at all.) to go with it (total base damage/range: 15/325)<br>
<br>
Aside from all this, attend Kael raids and get your Thurg quest armor.<br>
<br>
<br>
